Body with 60p+2a+T (
holotype
) rings; 
paratypes
with 34–52p+5a+T (males) or 44–57p+2–6a+T (females). Eye patches transversely ovoid, each composed of 7–11 blackish, rather flat ommatidia in 3–5 irregular longitudinal rows (
Fig. 1A
). Antennae rather short and clavate (
